---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is the character limit for a Twitch stream title?",
    answer: "The absolute character limit for a Twitch stream title is 140 characters. However, it is highly recommended to keep the title under 50-60 characters so it does not get cut off in the Twitch directory grid listing."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I edit my stream title during a live stream?",
    answer: "Yes, you can update your stream title at any time while live. You can change it via the Creator Dashboard, Twitch Chat commands (using '/title [your title]'), or directly inside your streaming software (like OBS Studio)."
  },
  {
    question: "Are emojis allowed in Twitch titles?",
    answer: "Yes, standard Unicode emojis are fully supported in Twitch stream titles. They are useful for grabbing attention in the directory list."
  },
  {
    question: "How do bracket tags help my stream search CTR?",
    answer: "Bracket tags (like '[ENG]', '[No Backseating]', '[100% Completion]') give viewers instant context about your stream rules, spoken language, or gameplay style before they click."
  },
  {
    question: "Is this Twitch title generator free to use?",
    answer: "Yes, this generator is completely free. You can generate unlimited stream title options for any game category or topic without logging in."
  }
];
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Twitch Title Generator - Cool & Catchy Stream Ideas"
  description="Generate cool, catchy, and clickbait Twitch titles. Optimize titles for Valorant, Just Chatting, and casual gaming streams to boost CTR."
  toolName="Twitch Title Generator"
  toolDescription="Create unique, high-CTR Twitch stream titles. Customize by stream style, toggle bracket tags, and preview inside a live directory stream card."
  category="Writing Tools"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <div slot="calculator" class="calc-card glass">
    <!-- Main Advanced Grid Layout -->
    <div class="calc-grid">
      <!-- Left Column: Generator Inputs -->
      <div class="calc-form-column">
        <div class="calc-form">
          <!-- Game Name Input -->
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="seed-input" class="icon-label">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="field-icon">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.75 5.25a3 3 0 0 1 3 3m3 0a6 6 0 0 1-7.029 5.912c-.563-.097-1.159.026-1.563.43L10.5 17.25H8.25v2.25H6v2.25H2.25v-2.818c0-.597.237-1.17.659-1.591l6.499-6.499c.404-.404.527-1 .43-1.563A6 6 0 1 1 21.75 8.25Z" />
              </svg>
              Stream Game or Topic
            </label>
            <input type="text" id="seed-input" class="form-input" placeholder="e.g. Valorant, Just Chatting, Elden Ring" value="Valorant" />
          </div>

          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem;">
            <!-- Stream Niche Style -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="niche-select" class="icon-label">Stream Vibe</label>
              <select id="niche-select" class="form-input" style="height: 48px; background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 0 12px; color: var(--color-text);">
                <option value="gaming">Competitive / Ranked Grind</option>
                <option value="casual">Chill / Casual Playthrough</option>
                <option value="cozy">Cozy / Just Chatting</option>
                <option value="creative">Creative / Coding / Art</option>
                <option value="funny">Humorous / Funny / Troll</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <!-- Hooks Dropdown -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="hook-select" class="icon-label">Hooks Style</label>
              <select id="hook-select" class="form-input" style="height: 48px; background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 0 12px; color: var(--color-text);">
                <option value="none">None (Clean)</option>
                <option value="hype">Clickbait / Hype ([INSANE])</option>
                <option value="question">Question / Mystery (?)</option>
                <option value="challenge">Challenge (Speedrun, 100%)</option>
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Checkbox Toggles -->
          <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; background: var(--color-bg-alt); padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
            <span style="font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-muted); text-transform: uppercase;">Aesthetic Details</span>
            
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.88rem;">
              <label style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text);">
                <input type="checkbox" id="emoji-check" checked style="accent-color: var(--color-brand); width: 16px; height: 16px;" />
                Include Emojis
              </label>
              <label style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text);">
                <input type="checkbox" id="tags-check" checked style="accent-color: var(--color-brand); width: 16px; height: 16px;" />
                Include Bracket Tags (e.g. [ENG], [DropsOn])
              </label>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Actions -->
          <div class="form-actions">
            <button type="button" id="generate-btn" class="calc-btn">Generate Titles</button>
            <button type="button" id="reset-btn" class="calc-btn-secondary">Reset Inputs</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right Column: Live Mockup Card -->
      <div class="calc-editor-column">
        <!-- Live Twitch Directory Stream Card Mockup -->
        <div class="twitch-stream-card glass" style="background: #18181b; color: #efeff1; border-radius: 16px; overflow: hidden; max-width: 300px; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%; border: 1px solid #2f2f35; text-align: left; box-shadow: var(--shadow-md); font-family: var(--font-body);">
          <!-- Stream Preview Box -->
          <div style="position: relative; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #9146ff, #6441a5); height: 160px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 700; color: #ffffff; user-select: none;">
            <span>Live Stream Preview</span>
            
            <!-- Live Badge -->
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 8px; left: 8px; background: #eb0400; color: #ffffff; font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 700; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;">Live</div>
            
            <!-- Viewer Count Badge -->
            <div style="position: absolute; bottom: 8px; left: 8px; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.6); color: #ffffff; font-size: 0.68rem; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">1.4K viewers</div>
          </div>

          <!-- Card Info Footer -->
          <div style="padding: 0.75rem; display: flex; gap: 8px; align-items: flex-start;">
            <!-- Avatar -->
            <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 50%; background: #9146ff; color: #ffffff; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 800; flex-shrink: 0;">
              CF
            </div>

            <!-- Text Blocks -->
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2px; min-width: 0; flex-grow: 1;">
              <!-- Stream Title -->
              <span id="mockup-stream-title" style="font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; color: #ffffff; display: -webkit-box; -webkit-line-clamp: 2; -webkit-box-orient: vertical; overflow: hidden; line-height: 1.35; min-height: 34px;">
                Grinding Rank in Valorant! 🚀 [DropsOn] [ENG]
              </span>
              
              <!-- Streamer Name -->
              <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #adadb8;">CreatorsFeel</span>
              
              <!-- Game category -->
              <span id="mockup-stream-game" style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #adadb8;">Valorant</span>

              <!-- Dynamic Tags -->
              <div style="display: flex; gap: 4px; margin-top: 4px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
                <span style="font-size: 0.62rem; background: #2f2f35; color: #adadb8; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 12px; font-weight: 700;">English</span>
                <span style="font-size: 0.62rem; background: #2f2f35; color: #adadb8; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 12px; font-weight: 700;">DropsEnabled</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Generated Results Section -->
    <div id="results-wrapper" class="hidden" style="margin-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px dashed var(--color-border); padding-top: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0 0 1rem 0; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; color: var(--color-brand);">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12c0 1.268-.63 2.39-1.593 3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043 3.296 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-3.296 1.043A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 12 21c-1.268 0-2.39-.63-3.068-1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1-3.296-1.043 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043-3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 3 12c0-1.268.63-2.39 1.593-3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1 1.043-3.296 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296-1.043A3.746 3.746 0 0 1 12 3c1.268 0 2.39.63 3.068 1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296 1.043 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 1.043 3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 21 12Z" />
        </svg>
        Suggested Twitch Titles
      </h3>

      <div class="usernames-grid" id="generated-titles-container">
        <!-- Results dynamic content goes here -->
      </div>

      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        <button type="button" id="generate-more-btn" class="calc-btn" style="max-width: 200px; padding: 0 1.5rem;">Generate More</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div slot="about" class="editorial-content">
    <h2>Twitch Title Generator: Write High Click-Through Rate Stream Titles</h2>
    <div style="margin: 1.5rem 0; background: var(--color-bg-alt); padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-brand);">
      <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        📺 <strong>Need to verify length rules for video metadata?</strong> Try our free <a href="/tools/youtube-title-length-checker" style="color: var(--color-brand); text-decoration: underline;">YouTube Title Length Checker</a> to verify search compliance and crop safety.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
      In Twitch's highly competitive directory, click-through rate (CTR) determines how fast your channel grows. Streamers compete side-by-side in thumbnail grids where the stream preview and the stream title are the only ways to hook a viewer's attention. A generic title like "gaming stream" will be overlooked, but a highly compelling, optimized title increases natural search discovery. Our free <strong>twitch title generator</strong> is built to construct attention-grabbing stream titles that increase CTR and match search queries naturally.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Use This Tool</h3>
    <p>
      To write and audit custom Twitch stream titles in real-time, follow these simple directions:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Game or Topic:</strong> Enter your stream's category or game name (e.g. Valorant, Just Chatting, Minecraft).</li>
      <li><strong>Stream Vibe:</strong> Pick a tone style matching your stream (Competitive, Casual, Cozy, Creative, or Funny).</li>
      <li><strong>Hooks Selection:</strong> Select a power word hook structure (Hype/Clickbait, Question/Mystery, or Challenge).</li>
      <li><strong>Toggles:</strong> Check options to insert emojis or bracketed tags (like [DropsEnabled], [ENG], [No Backseating]).</li>
      <li><strong>Generate List:</strong> Click <strong>Generate Titles</strong> to create 15 custom options.</li>
      <li><strong>Preview & Copy:</strong> Click any title to preview it inside the Twitch card mockup, and click the copy chip button. Click <strong>Generate More</strong> to append 5 more options.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>What is Twitch Title</h3>
    <p>
      A <strong>Twitch title</strong> is the descriptive header displayed on your live broadcast. The absolute limit set by Twitch is 140 characters. However, because directory layouts truncate text after 50 to 60 characters on desktop and mobile screens, placing your core hooks and tags at the start of your <strong>twitch titles</strong> is crucial. Optimizing these titles improves click-through rate and ensures your stream is easily discoverable in search.
    </p>

    <h3>How Does It Work?</h3>
    <p>
      The generator merges your game category with hook layouts:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Hook Placement:</strong> Positions attention-grabbing hooks at the start of the title to avoid directory cropping.</li>
      <li><strong>Bracket Tag Injections:</strong> Appends tags at the end of the title, like language markers or stream rules.</li>
      <li><strong>Size Audit:</strong> Keeps titles under the 140-character limit, highlighting crop risk if they exceed 60 characters.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Example Calculation</h3>
    <p>
      Let's look at how a Twitch title character budget is calculated:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Input Game:</strong> `"Valorant"`<br />
      <strong>Stream Niche selected:</strong> `"Competitive / Ranked Grind"`<br />
      <strong>Hooks Style:</strong> `"Clickbait / Hype"`<br />
      <strong>Toggles:</strong> `"Include Emojis"`, `"Include Bracket Tags"`
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Calculation Process:</strong><br />
      ✦ Hype prefix: `"[INSANE]"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>8 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Base hook: `"Grinding to Radiant in Valorant!"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>33 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Emojis: `"🚀🔥"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>4 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Bracket tags: `"[ENG] [DropsEnabled]"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>20 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Combined output: `"[INSANE] Grinding to Radiant in Valorant! 🚀🔥 [ENG] [DropsEnabled]"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>65 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Character budget check: `65 < 140 characters` (strictly compliant).
    </p>
    <p>
      The generated title fits within Twitch's limits. Placing the clickbait prefix at the front ensures it is visible in directory layouts.
    </p>

    <h3>Who Should Use This Tool?</h3>
    <p>
      This generator is designed for:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Competitive Gamers:</strong> Streaming ranked climbs, tournaments, or high-tier play (e.g. `[HYPE] Grinding to Radiant in Valorant!`).</li>
      <li><strong>Just Chatting Streamers:</strong> Writing cozy chat setups, AMA streams, or podcast discussions (e.g. `Cozy Sunday AMA! ☕ [ENG]`).</li>
      <li><strong>Speedrunners & Challenge Streamers:</strong> Sharing speedruns or 100% completion challenges (e.g. `Elden Ring Speedrun Challenge! ⚔️`).</li>
      <li><strong>Creative Tech Streamers:</strong> Broadcasting software development, digital art, or hardware builds (e.g. `Building custom apps in Rust! 💻`).</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

